## 📌 Project Overview

The **Mobile Sales Dashboard** is an interactive Power BI project designed to analyze mobile phone sales performance across different brands, cities, payment methods, and time periods.

It transforms raw sales data into actionable business insights through dynamic visualizations, KPIs, and filtering capabilities — enabling fast, data-driven decision-making.

---

## 🖥️ Dashboard Preview

![Mobile Sales Dashboard](dashboard_preview.png)

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- 📊 Analyze overall mobile sales performance
- 📅 Track sales trends across months and weekdays
- 🏷️ Compare sales among different mobile brands
- ⭐ Evaluate customer rating distribution
- 💳 Understand payment method preferences
- 🗺️ Identify top-performing cities and regions

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| **Power BI Desktop** | Dashboard development & visualization |
| **Power Query** | Data cleaning & transformation |
| **DAX** | Custom measures & calculations |
| **Data Modeling** | Relational data structure |
| **Microsoft Excel** | Data source |

---

## 📊 Dashboard Features

### 🔹 KPI Cards
| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Total Sales | ₹769.20M |
| Total Quantity Sold | 153.84M |
| Total Transactions | 4K |
| Average Price | ₹40.11K |

### 🔹 Interactive Filters (Slicers)
- Brand
- Mobile Model
- Payment Method
- Month Selection
- Clear All Filters Button

### 🔹 Visualizations
- 🥧 **Pie Chart** — Total Transactions by Payment Method
- 🗺️ **Map Visual** — Total Quantity by City
- 📊 **Bar Chart** — Total Sales by Mobile Model
- 🔻 **Funnel Chart** — Customer Ratings Distribution
- 📈 **Line Chart** — Total Sales by Day Name
- 📈 **Line Chart** — Total Quantity by Month
- 📋 **Table** — Brand-wise Sales & Transactions

---

## 📈 Key Insights

- ✅ Analyzed **₹769M+ Total Sales** across all brands and regions
- ✅ Identified **top-selling mobile models** (iPhone SE, OnePlus Nord, Galaxy Note 20)
- ✅ Evaluated **customer rating trends** (Good / Average / Poor)
- ✅ Analyzed **sales performance across cities** using map visualization
- ✅ Compared **payment method usage** — Cash, UPI, Credit Card & Debit Card are nearly equal (~24–26% each)
- ✅ Tracked **monthly and daily sales patterns** with line charts

---

## 🧮 DAX Measures

```dax
Total Sales = SUM(Sales[Total_Sales])

Total Quantity = SUM(Sales[Quantity])

Total Transactions = COUNT(Sales[Transaction_ID])

Average Price = DIVIDE([Total Sales], [Total Quantity])
```

---

## 🗂️ Data Model

The project follows a structured star schema connecting:

```
Sales Data (Fact Table)
    ├── Product Information
    ├── Customer Ratings
    ├── Payment Details
    └── Geographic Data
```

